The Mappings tab provides an overview of all created data schemas that are associated with data schemas. It consists of two main areas:

![](data:image/png;base64,)Mappings tab

- **Top toolbar** with **search field**

- **Table area **containing all existing Mappings

The table in the Mappings tab contains the following columns:

Field

Description

**Title**

Name of the data schema

**Project**

Name of the Project associated with the data schema

**Status**

Validation status of the data schema

**Date modified**

Date and time when the data schema was last modified

> Tip: Sort and search

The Mappings table can be searched and sorted to easily find a particular Mapping. Use the full-text search field to search by **Title **or **Date modified**.

Click on a column header to sort that column in ascending or descending order. Click again to change the sorting or return to the default sorting.

## User actions on Mappings
The following actions can be performed from the Mappings tab:

- **Edit an existing Mapping **by clicking the **Edit** button (appears on mouseover)
